<br>
Let's start out with the classic.<br>
<br>
Ultima Online<br>
<br>
Pros:<br>
1.  Housing (No other game has gone as far to make the player feel he is part of the game.)<br>
2. Mounts (Always a part of UO, cheap, effective, nuff said)<br>
3. PKin' in the beginning(It was a part of life, you packed light, and, always traveled with friends)<br>
4. Soloing (Later in the game, it became a big way to make money)<br>
5. Trade Skills (They were very useful from the get go, blacksmiths were easily rich quickly)<br>
<br>
Cons<br>
1. Grief players (Because of the not so harsh rules in UO, it was easy to ruin other people's day)<br>
2. Lag (It got you dead, more so then any other game I have played)<br>
3. The age of players(It ranged in UO, considering when I played it, it had no competition, but, after school let out, UO's general IQ dropped)<br>
4.Soloing(Yeah, when you can kill any monster in the game by yourself, you get jaded as to the strength of anything.)<br>
5.The facet split(When UO decided that they were done listening to whining, they split the servers so each had two copies of the world, one was PVP and the other wasn't, that gave a lot of people a reason to quit.)<br>
<br>
EverQuest:<br>
 <br>
Pros:<br>
1. 3D(I think it is anyone, going from UO to EQ was like watching a game from above to being captivated by it)<br>
2. Classes/races (When I learned I could choose something more then just my color on a game...I flipped.)<br>
3. Community(Actually getting rewarded for being nice, who'da thunk it?!)<br>
4. Expansions(A game that can constantly progress without pissing off half it's fan base is nice.)<br>
5. Grouping(Classes actually accented eachother, wow)<br>
<br>
Cons:<br>
1. Questing(Let's face it, they aren't that great, for the most part.  How many crushbone belts can one guy need.  Seriously.)<br>
2. Exp grind (Unless you find a way to cheat it -glare-, it can be something you wish you never had to sit thru)<br>
3. People who suck (Although this happens in everygame, it seems to have more of an impact on EQ because of the reputation people have to keep up)<br>
4. Computer Reqs (It keeps getting harder to play due to having to upgrade the computer right along with the game)<br>
5. Nerfing (=P)<br>
<br>
Dark Ages of Camelot<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> Haven't played it as much, so, less to talk about)<br>
<br>
Pros:<br>
<br>
1. It's historical fantasy(That's cool, I like being able to visit Stone Henge<br>
2.Skill based leveling (It's cool when chars can develop differently using the same class)<br>
3. Not such a big basis on equipment(Not much uber loot, or so I hear)<br>
<br>
Cons:<br>
<br>
1. High end content mostly PvP,(no real high end PvM encounters, last I heard)<br>
2. Quests(No one has really gotten them right yet.  Not good enough for my liking, always takes time to run around to all corners, not all that exciting.<br>
3. Graphics (I don't like them, not my kind of look)<br>
<br>
Anarchy Online:<br>
<br>
1. Setting/Story: (Great background story, kept up by an actual cartoon seris.)<br>
2. Genre:  (Sci-Fi &gt; Fantasy in some ways to me, shooting guns is fun, what can I say?)<br>
3. Classes: (They make sense, and what beats a guy with a huge robot?)<br>
4.Missions(Great idea, in my opinion, being able to go thru and do something with your group that won't be interefered with.)<br>
<br>
Cons:<br>
1. Age of players (This game is where a lot of the kewl doods decided they would hang out.  I couldn't go a day without seeing someone being an idiot.)<br>
2. High end content (Again, a major focus on PvP, no real high end content, as of when I left)<br>
3. Bugs(This game outdid a lot of others in the problems area (Sans WWIIO, which was said to be released about a year before it was ready) and, rightly so)<br>
4. Equipment ( A lot of it is easily attainable and therefore lacks the feeling of accomplishment behind obtaining it)<br>
<br>
<br>
Feel free to add more games or more comments.  That killed some time though.<br>
